Diagram 1 (The Hane Fails)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Let's start by following the proverb which states, "there's death in a hane,". Black hanes at 1.
\par
\par Don't follow proverbs blindly. If you try to always think about every situation in terms of a proverb, then the proverbs are no longer guides, but instead poison your mind.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj White plays 2, \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , or \b\f1 B \b0\f0 and lives easily.
\par
\par Black has failed.
\par }
