Diagram 2 (Calm Response)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's clamp at 1 is a creative idea.
\par
\par However, white 2 is a calm move, and the clamp does not work.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Instead of 2, if white had played dansu from the direction of 3, because white can't fill in at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white drops dead.
\par
\par Black must have expected this result when the clamp was played.
\par }
