Diagram 4 (White's Correct Move)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj In the beginning, it is right for white to extend at 1 instead of playing \b\f1 A\b0\f0 . This secures the life of white's group.
\par \pard
